caption: I love Cousin John’s. I have been a customer since 1979!!  Delicious food, friendly stand, the best bakery in Park Slope. You have to try their strawberry cream cake. It’s the best. And they always have a deal buy one get one free after 7 PM. They also make great cranberry zucchini and blueberry muffins. You won’t be disappointed.

Thanks So Much!

Asked to give up the scone and order something off the menu instead, the waitress pleasantly accepted the idea with a smile. The egg & cheese sandwich with multigrain bread was absolutely amazing. It's definitely nothing simple and blew me away. I was too full, otherwise really wanted to give the apple pie a try.

It has been many, many years since I have dined at Cousin John's Cafe.  Over twenty years to be exact... My son worked there about twenty years ago and therein is a staple of memorable moments. The deserts and meals are still loving to the soul. New selections have been added, but the heart and spirit of the eatery is a welcome breeze of fresh air, and we are grateful.

It's a good brunch, but definitely feels like eating in a bakery. Because of the less formal restaurant setting the prices are very reasonable for brunch, although they feel right for the place. They do egg dishes and stuff, so it's not just bakery food for brunch. The seating area is tiny and pretty cramped. The free chocolate bread with preserves is really great, the bread is fresh and soft and nicely chocolatey, but not overwhelming. The egg dishes are large, and come with the option of a croissant, which is also huge. The cheese blintzes are rich and very filled, and surrounded by preserves and whipped cream. The espresso drinks, at least the latte, tasted burnt, but it was strong, if not the tastiest coffee drink. The service is good, and we didn't feel rushed, if anything the service was a bit slow, but that was fine. Some bike parking outside would be nice. There's a bus stop right outside, and it's an easy walk from Grand Army Plaza. The bakery selection is impressive and it all looks good, and the croissant was good if that's some indication. If you eat there you can see them making everything right in the back, it's all fresh-made in-house, and they seem to be going constantly.

Love their black and white cookies. The cookies aren't cheap but are definitely worth getting. I've tried a few of their cakes as well which are also good but the cookies are my personal favorite. The service is good even during peak times which I appreciate. I wish they had more seating but if you're not planning on dining it this wont be a problem.
excellent bakery.Awfully small but still a good place for breakfast if you don't mind the bathroom. Staff friendly and cheerful.

I only bought one cake from here while attending a birthday party of a close friend in the neighborhood. I was tasked to bring a gluten-free birthday cake, so I got the flourless chocolate cake from Cousin Johns.  It was the hit of the party. The cake competed among several other desserts people brought in but this one "took the cake" and was gone within 15 minutes while the other desserts languished throughout the night. If the quality of their goods are at the same level as their flourless chocolate cake, you will not be disappointed.
I love it so much
I get my cakes from Cousin John's they are alwayz Fresh and when u ask them to put some almonds around it the cake taste even Better luv it every time!!!!
Love their pastries
The food here is great and the service is even better. This cafe just needs a bigger space and it will be perfect.

We got a range of goodies from here, some tarts, a brownie, some some oatmeal cookies to share with some friends. The tarts were ok, although the raspberry definitely outshone the apple. The brownie was a little dry and didn't really have anything exciting going on. I wasn't over the moon about the cookies either, but our friend who prefers oatmeal couldn't stop raving about them so I assume they were a hit for people who care about the cookie. If you're in the area, drop by, but don't go out of your way.

I've been going to Cousin John's Bakery for years and never had one complaint about the place. The cakes are nicely decorated and taste delicious. I mainly come to get the brownies, cannoli's and tarts which are all incredible. It's a nice cozy bakery/cafe though, very small and maybe about 4 tables to sit at but that's not a problem for me at all.
Cakes are mostly frosting, barely any cake at all. To make matters worse, the frosting is super sweet and just doesn't taste good. I won't be returning.
Amazing food & amazing service at an amazing price!

With all the famous bakeries out there, it's nice to see a neighborhood one that can stand on its own. Cousin John's is a cute cafe and bakery. Great place to pick up a birthday cake, pies for dessert, and cookies just to munch on. They also serve lunch and brunch. The tables are for restaurant service. You can't really lounge.

Great breakfast place. The croissants are best I've had in the city, prices are pretty unbelievable considering it's in the heart of park slope (under $6 for most), and it's very homey. Plus, you have get the bonus of being able to check out some beautiful and delicious cakes they make in the open area behind the tables.

Very small, but very fresh and delicious bakery.  Come here for brunch as much as we can, and ALWAYS get a croissant.  Boyfriend has said, "This place is to croissants as Pies n' Thighs is to biscuits," therefore a high recommendation.  Also, VERY affordable!  More so than any brooklyn brunch place.  Very small, homey, and you'll want to buy EVERY pastry in the place.

I'm not just giving Cousin John's a "Best Ever" because I used to work here weekends during grad school, but because everything they have is divine. Yes, it's not cheap, but it's DELICIOUS. Whether it's the angel food cake or the cheesecake or even the apple crisp, you won't be disappointed. You also won't find a cheaper brunch anywhere; but beware, no alcohol, just perfectly brewed beverages.  CJ's cheesecake is better than Junior's and you won't find a better angel cake ANYWHERE!
Absolutely yummy.
Everything is great except for the radio blaring annoying pop music in the back.
DELICIOUS. cheesecake and angel cake fabulous,. Good customer service.
Terrible service and it takes almost 45 minutes on a slow day to get your food.
Their cupcakes were so dry. Omg!
Cheap brunch including whole wheat pancakes, belgian waffles, eggs benedict. Also the mocha squares are really good.
